rdfs:label: continuant
IAO:0000115: An entity that exists in full at any time in which it exists at all, persists through time while maintaining its identity and has no temporal parts.

rdfs:label: occurrent
IAO:0000115: An entity that has temporal parts and that happens, unfolds or develops through time.

rdfs:label: symptom
IAO:0000115: A quality of a patient that is observed by the patient or a processual entity experienced by the patient, either of which is hypothesized by the patient to be a realization of a disease.

rdfs:label: independent continuant
IAO:0000115: A continuant that is a bearer of quality and realizable entity entities, in which other entities inhere and which itself cannot inhere in anything.

rdfs:label: specifically dependent continuant
IAO:0000115: A continuant that inheres in or is borne by other entities. Every instance of A requires some specific instance of B which must always be the same.

rdfs:label: generically dependent continuant
IAO:0000115: A continuant that is dependent on one or other independent continuant bearers. For every instance of A requires some instance of (an independent continuant type) B but which instance of B serves can change from time to time.

rdfs:label: process
IAO:0000115: An occurrent that has temporal proper parts and for some time t, p s-depends_on some material entity at t.

rdfs:label: process boundary
IAO:0000115: p is a process boundary =Def. p is a temporal part of a process & p has no proper temporal parts. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [084-001])

rdfs:label: material entity
IAO:0000115: An independent continuant that is spatially extended whose identity is independent of that of other entities and can be maintained through time.

rdfs:label: realizable entity
IAO:0000115: A specifically dependent continuant  that inheres in continuant  entities and are not exhibited in full at every time in which it inheres in an entity or group of entities. The exhibition or actualization of a realizable entity is a particular manifestation, functioning or process that occurs under certain circumstances.

rdfs:label: process profile
IAO:0000115: b is a process_profile =Def. there is some process c such that b process_profile_of c (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [093-002])

rdfs:label: biological_process
IAO:0000115: Any process specifically pertinent to the functioning of integrated living units: cells, tissues, organs, and organisms. A process is a collection of molecular events with a defined beginning and end.

rdfs:label: biological regulation
IAO:0000115: Any process that modulates a measurable attribute of any biological process, quality or function.

rdfs:label: immunization against infectious agent
IAO:0000115: A process by which an organism acquires immunity to an infectious agent.

rdfs:label: infectious disease epidemic
IAO:0000115: A process of infectious disease realizations and for which there is a statistically significant increase in the infectious disease incidence of a population.

rdfs:label: infectious disease pandemic
IAO:0000115: A process in which multiple infectious disease epidemics of the same type of infectious disease unfold over overlapping periods of time and affect organism populations located in different geographic regions, including different countries and continents.

rdfs:label: process of establishing an infection
IAO:0000115: A process by which an infectious agent, established in a host, becomes part of an infection in the host.

rdfs:label: production
IAO:0000115: A process in which an entity comes into being as a result of the process.

rdfs:label: immunosuppression
IAO:0000115: A process that attenuates an immune response.

rdfs:label: appearance of disorder
IAO:0000115: A process by which a disorder comes into existence.

rdfs:label: sepsis
IAO:0000115: A process that is a systemic inflammatory response to infection.

rdfs:label: process that results in death
IAO:0000115: A process that results in death.

rdfs:label: host exposure to infectious agent
IAO:0000115: A process in which a potential host of an infectious agent is exposed to an infectious agent.

rdfs:label: transition to clinical abnormality
IAO:0000115: A process by which a part of an organism or something contained in an organism becomes clinically abnormal.

rdfs:label: disease course
IAO:0000115: The totality of all processes through which a given disease instance is realized.

rdfs:label: transmission process
IAO:0000115: A process that is the means during which the pathogen is transmitted directly or indirectly from its natural reservoir, a susceptible host or source to a new host.

rdfs:label: life-death temporal boundary
IAO:0000115: A life cycle temporal boundary that marks the end of the life cycle of the organism.

rdfs:label: anatomical entity
IAO:0000115: A part of a multicellular organism that is either an immaterial entity or a material entity with granularity above the level of a protein complex.  Or, a substance produced by a multicellular organism with granularity above the level of a protein complex.

rdfs:label: molecular entity
IAO:0000115: Any constitutionally or isotopically distinct atom, molecule, ion, ion pair, radical, radical ion, complex, conformer etc., identifiable as a separately distinguishable entity.

rdfs:label: macromolecular complex
IAO:0000115: A stable assembly of two or more macromolecules, i.e. proteins, nucleic acids, carbohydrates or lipids, in which at least one component is a protein and the constituent parts function together.

rdfs:label: pathogen
IAO:0000115: A material entity with a pathogenic disposition.

rdfs:label: vehicle of infectious agent
IAO:0000115: A material entity bearing an infectious agent vehicle role.

rdfs:label: infectious agent reservoir
IAO:0000115: A material entity bearing an infectious agent reservoir role.

rdfs:label: disinfectant
IAO:0000115: A material entity bearing a disinfectant role.

rdfs:label: antiseptic
IAO:0000115: A material entity bearing an antiseptic role.

rdfs:label: antimicrobial
IAO:0000115: A material entity with an antimicrobial disposition.

rdfs:label: antiviral
IAO:0000115: A material entity bearing an antiviral disposition.

rdfs:label: antifungal
IAO:0000115: A material entity bearing an antifungal disposition.

rdfs:label: antiparasitic
IAO:0000115: A material entity bearing an antiparasitic disposition.

rdfs:label: antibacterial
IAO:0000115: A material entity bearing an antibacterial disposition.

rdfs:label: resistant entity
IAO:0000115: A material entity that has a resistance disposition.

rdfs:label: infection
IAO:0000115: A part of an extended organism that itself has as part a population of one or more infectious agents and that (1) exists as a result of processes initiated by members of the infectious agent population and is (2) clinically abnormal in virtue of the presence of this infectious agent population, or (3) has a disposition to bring clinical abnormality to immunocompetent organisms of the same Species as the host (the organism corresponding to the extended organism) through transmission of a member or offspring of a member of the infectious agent population.

rdfs:label: source of infection
IAO:0000115: A material entity bearing a source of infection role.

rdfs:label: organism
IAO:0000115: A material entity that is an individual living system, such as animal, plant, bacteria or virus, that is capable of replicating or reproducing, growth and maintenance in the right environment. An organism may be unicellular or made up, like humans, of many billions of cells divided into specialized tissues and organs.

rdfs:label: disorder
IAO:0000115: A material entity which is clinically abnormal and part of an extended organism. Disorders are the physical basis of disease.

rdfs:label: continuant fiat boundary
IAO:0000115: b is a continuant fiat boundary = Def. b is an immaterial entity that is of zero, one or two dimensions and does not include a spatial region as part. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [029-001])

rdfs:label: role
IAO:0000115: A realizable entity  the manifestation of which brings about some result or end that is not essential to a continuant  in virtue of the kind of thing that it is but that can be served or participated in by that kind of continuant  in some kinds of natural, social or institutional contexts.

rdfs:label: relational quality
IAO:0000115: b is a relational quality = Def. for some independent continuants c, d and for some time t: b quality_of c at t & b quality_of d at t. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [057-001])

rdfs:label: infectious agent transmissibility
IAO:0000115: A quality that inheres in an infectious agent and is the likelihood that the infectious agent will undergo a horizontal transmission process.

rdfs:label: infectivity
IAO:0000115: A quality that inheres in an infectious agent and is the liklihood that the infectious disposition will be realized upon exposure of a susceptible organism.

rdfs:label: virulence
IAO:0000115: A quality that inheres in an infectious agent and is the degree to which realizations of the infectious disease caused by the infectious agent become severe or fatal.

rdfs:label: susceptibility
IAO:0000115: A quality that inheres in an entity and is the degree to which it can be harmed by another entity.

rdfs:label: infectious disease incidence
IAO:0000115: A quality that inheres in an organism population and is the number of realizations of an infectious disease for which the infectious disease course begins during a specified period of time.

rdfs:label: infection incidence
IAO:0000115: A quality that inheres in an organism population and is the number of organisms in the population that become infected with an infectious agent during a specified period of time.

rdfs:label: infectious disease incidence proportion
IAO:0000115: A quality that inheres in an organism population and is the proportion of members of the population not experiencing an infectious disease course at the beginning of a specified period of time and in whom the infectious disease begins during the specified period of time.

rdfs:label: infection incidence proportion
IAO:0000115: A quality that inheres in an organism population and is the proportion of members of the population not infected at the beginning of a specified period of time who become infected during the specified period of time.

rdfs:label: infectious disease incidence rate
IAO:0000115: A quality that inheres in an organism population and is the infectious disease incidence proportion per unit time.

rdfs:label: infection incidence rate
IAO:0000115: A quality that inheres in an organism population and is the infection incidence proportion per unit time.

rdfs:label: infectious disease prevalence
IAO:0000115: A quality that inheres in an organism population and is the number of realizations of an infectious disease in the population at a specified time.

rdfs:label: infection prevalence
IAO:0000115: A quality that inheres in an organism population and is the number of organisms in the population infected with an infectious agent at a specified time.

rdfs:label: infectious disease lifetime prevalence
IAO:0000115: A quality that inheres in an organism population and is the number of organisms in the population who have, at any point during their lives, been bearers of an infectious disease and experienced realization of the disease.

rdfs:label: infectious agent seroprevalence
IAO:0000115: A quality that inheres in an organism population and is the number of organisms in the population that have antibody specific for an infectious agent in their serum at a specified time.

rdfs:label: infectious disease mortality rate
IAO:0000115: A quality that inheres in an organism population and is the per capita number of deaths in the population resulting from an infectious disease over a specified period of time.

rdfs:label: infectious disease endemicity
IAO:0000115: A quality that inheres in an organism population in virtue of the fact that infections of the type that causes an infectious disease are maintained in the population via intra-population transmission or by transmission from a local reservoir.

rdfs:label: infectious disease sporadicity
IAO:0000115: A quality that inheres in an organism population by virtue of the fact that realizations of an infectious disease occur in the population with a fluctuating prevalence.

rdfs:label: incubation period
IAO:0000115: A continuous temporal interval beginning with the extablishment of an infectious agent colony and ending with the onset of symptoms (or infectious disease course?).

rdfs:label: communicability period
IAO:0000115: A continuous temporal interval during which an infectious agent host bears a contagiousness disposition.

rdfs:label: transmission period
IAO:0000115: A continuous temporal interval during which a transmission process occurs.

rdfs:label: reproduction
IAO:0000115: The production of new individuals that contain some portion of genetic material inherited from one or more parent organisms.

rdfs:label: immune response
IAO:0000115: Any immune system process that functions in the calibrated response of an organism to a potential internal or invasive threat.

rdfs:label: developmental process
IAO:0000115: A biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of an integrated living unit: an anatomical structure (which may be a subcellular structure, cell, tissue, or organ), or organism over time from an initial condition to a later condition.

rdfs:label: growth
IAO:0000115: The increase in size or mass of an entire organism, a part of an organism or a cell.

rdfs:label: adhesion of symbiont to host
IAO:0000115: The attachment of a symbiont to its host via adhesion molecules, general stickiness etc., either directly or indirectly. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

rdfs:label: establishment of localization
IAO:0000115: Any process that localizes a substance or cellular component. This may occur via movement, tethering or selective degradation.

rdfs:label: multi-organism process
IAO:0000115: A biological process which involves another organism of the same or different species.

rdfs:label: life-sustaining process
IAO:0000115: A process which is necessary for the survival of an organism.

rdfs:label: negative regulation of viral process
IAO:0000115: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of a multi-organism process in which a virus is a participant.

rdfs:label: negative regulation of immune response
IAO:0000115: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the immune response, the immunological reaction of an organism to an immunogenic stimulus.

rdfs:label: negative regulation of developmental process
IAO:0000115: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the rate or extent of development, the biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of an organism over time from an initial condition (e.g. a zygote, or a young adult) to a later condition (e.g. a multicellular animal or an aged adult).

rdfs:label: negative regulation of life-sustaining process
IAO:0000115: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of a life-sustaining process.

rdfs:label: active immunization against infectious agent
IAO:0000115: An immunization that begins with exposure of an organism to antigen and results in immunity against an infectious agent.

rdfs:label: passive immunization against infectious agent
IAO:0000115: An immunization that begins with transfer to an organism of molecules not produced by that organism and that confer immunity against an infectious agent.

rdfs:label: replication
IAO:0000115: A production process in which a participant creates a copy of itself.

rdfs:label: physiologic immunosuppression
IAO:0000115: An immunosuppression which unfolds as part of the natural self-regulation of an immune response.

rdfs:label: pathologic immunosuppression
IAO:0000115: An immunosuppression process which arises as the result of a disorder.

rdfs:label: pregnancy-induced immunosuppression
IAO:0000115: An immunosuppression induced by progesterone and other factors upregulated in pregnant women.

rdfs:label: severe sepsis
IAO:0000115: A sepsis that results in organ dysfunction, hypotension, or hypofusion of at least one organ.

rdfs:label: direct host exposure to infectious agent
IAO:0000115: A process in which a potential host of an infectious agent comes into direct physical contact with the infectious agent.

rdfs:label: host exposure to environment containing infectious agent
IAO:0000115: A process in which a potential host of an infectious agent is exposed to an environment in which the infectious agent is present and physical contact between the two can occur, but such contact is not planned.

rdfs:label: infectious disease course
IAO:0000115: A disease course that is the realization of an infectious disease.

rdfs:label: horizontal pathogen transmission process
IAO:0000115: A pathogen transmission process in which a pathogen is transmitted from one host to another of the same Species, and the two hosts are not in a parent-child relationship.

rdfs:label: indirect
IAO:0000115: Indirect transmission is a transmission process during which the pathogen is indirectly transferred from a reservoir, source or host to another host by intermediary vehicles, vectors or as airborne dust particles.

rdfs:label: organism population
IAO:0000115: An aggregate of organisms of the same Species.

rdfs:label: extended organism
IAO:0000115: An object aggregate consisting of an organism and all material entities located within the organism, overlapping the organism, or occupying sites formed in part by the organism.

rdfs:label: cell
IAO:0000115: A material entity of anatomical origin (part of or deriving from an organism) that has as its parts a maximally connected cell compartment surrounded by a plasma membrane.

rdfs:label: infectious agent portal of entry
IAO:0000115: An anatomical entity bearing an infectious agent portal of entry role.

rdfs:label: infectious agent portal of exit
IAO:0000115: An anatomical entity bearing an infectious agent portal of exit role.

rdfs:label: blood
IAO:0000115: A fluid that is composed of blood plasma and erythrocytes.

rdfs:label: virulence factor
IAO:0000115: A biological macromolecule produced by a pathogen and that has a virulence factor disposition.

rdfs:label: invasion factor
IAO:0000115: A biological macromolecule that has an invasion disposition.

rdfs:label: toxin
IAO:0000115: A molecular entity that has a toxin disposition.

rdfs:label: adhesion factor
IAO:0000115: A biological macromolecule that has an adhesion disposition.

rdfs:label: immunoglobulin complex
IAO:0000115: A protein complex that in its canonical form is composed of two identical immunoglobulin heavy chains and two identical immunoglobulin light chains, held together by disulfide bonds and sometimes complexed with additional proteins. An immunoglobulin complex may be embedded in the plasma membrane or present in the extracellular space, in mucosal areas or other tissues, or circulating in the blood or lymph.

rdfs:label: B cell receptor complex
IAO:0000115: An immunoglobulin complex that is present in the plasma membrane of B cells and that in its canonical form is composed of two identical immunoglobulin heavy chains and two identical immunoglobulin light chains and a signaling subunit, a heterodimer of the Ig-alpha and Ig-beta proteins.

rdfs:label: T cell receptor complex
IAO:0000115: A protein complex that contains a disulfide-linked heterodimer of T cell receptor (TCR) chains, which are members of the immunoglobulin superfamily, and mediates antigen recognition, ultimately resulting in T cell activation. The TCR heterodimer is associated with the CD3 complex, which consists of the nonpolymorphic polypeptides gamma, delta, epsilon, zeta, and, in some cases, eta (an RNA splice variant of zeta) or Fc epsilon chains.

rdfs:label: infectious agent
IAO:0000115: An organism that has an infectious disposition.

rdfs:label: fomite
IAO:0000115: A material entity bearing a fomite role.

rdfs:label: microbicide
IAO:0000115: A material entity with an antimicrobial disposition that is realized in a process of killing microorganisms.

rdfs:label: microbistatic
IAO:0000115: A material entity with an antimicrobial disposition that is realized in a process of inhibiting the growth of microorganisms.

rdfs:label: viricide
IAO:0000115: A material entity with an antiviral disposition that is realized in a process of killing viruses.

rdfs:label: complex infection
IAO:0000115: An infection comprised of infectious organisms from different Species.

rdfs:label: extracellular infection
IAO:0000115: An infection for which the infectious agents that are part of the infection persist in the extracellular space of the host.

rdfs:label: intracellular infection
IAO:0000115: An infection for which the infectious agents that are part of the infection persist inside host cells.

rdfs:label: systemic infection
IAO:0000115: An infection for which the infectious agents that are part of the infection are distributed throughout the host.

rdfs:label: local infection
IAO:0000115: An infection for which the infectious agents that are part of the infection are limited to a relatively small area of the host's body.

rdfs:label: infectious disorder
IAO:0000115: An infection that is clinically abnormal.

rdfs:label: subclinical infection
IAO:0000115: An infection that is part of an asymptomatic host.

rdfs:label: chronic infection
IAO:0000115: An infection that persists for an extended period of time.

rdfs:label: hospital-acquired infection
IAO:0000115: An infection resulting from a transmission process that unfolds in a hospital.

rdfs:label: community-acquired infection
IAO:0000115: An infection resulting from a transmission process that did not unfold in a health care facility.

rdfs:label: metatstatic infection
IAO:0000115: An infection established as a result of spread from another infection in a non-adjacent location in the extended organism of the host.

rdfs:label: nursing-home acquired infection
IAO:0000115: An infection resulting from a transmission process that unfolds in a nursing home.

rdfs:label: simple infection
IAO:0000115: An infection comprised of infectious organisms all of the same Species.

rdfs:label: candidiasis
IAO:0000115: An infection that has as part organisms of the Genus Candida.

rdfs:label: trichomoniasis
IAO:0000115: An infection that has as part organisms of the Species Trichomonas vaginalis.

rdfs:label: leptospirosis
IAO:0000115: An infection that has as part organisms of the Genus Leptospira.

rdfs:label: Shigellosis
IAO:0000115: An infection located in the bowel and that has as part organisms of the Genus Shigella.

rdfs:label: amebiasis
IAO:0000115: An infection located in the colon and that has as part organisms of the Species Entamoeba histolytica

rdfs:label: immunosuppressed organism
IAO:0000115: An organism that is experiencing pregnancy-induced or pathologic immunosuppression.

rdfs:label: immunocompetent organism
IAO:0000115: An organism that has immunocompetence.

rdfs:label: colonized host
IAO:0000115: An organism that contains a colony in or on its extended organism.

rdfs:label: infected organism
IAO:0000115: An organism that has an infection in or on its extended organism.

rdfs:label: symbiont
IAO:0000115: An organism bearing a symbiont role.

rdfs:label: host
IAO:0000115: An organism bearing a host role.

rdfs:label: infectious agent vector
IAO:0000115: An organism bearing an infectious agent vector role.

rdfs:label: long-term non-progressor
IAO:0000115: An organism experiencing a long-term non-progressing infectious disease course.

rdfs:label: immunodeficient organism
IAO:0000115: An organism that has an immunodeficiency.

rdfs:label: potential host of infectious agent
IAO:0000115: An organism that has the capability to bear a host of infectious agent role.

rdfs:label: susceptible organism
IAO:0000115: An organism that is not infected with an infectious agent and lacks protective immunity to the infectious agent.

rdfs:label: immunodeficiency
IAO:0000115: A disorder of an immune system component that results in defective functioning of the immune system.

rdfs:label: virulence factor disposition
IAO:0000115: A disposition borne by a biological macromolecule produced by a pathogen that is a disposition to undergo processes that increase the pathogen's virulence.

rdfs:label: toxin disposition
IAO:0000115: A disposition to cause I) malfunction of cells, ii) damage to extracellular matrix, or iii) damage of cells to a degree that can result in cell death.

rdfs:label: adhesion disposition
IAO:0000115: A disposition borne by a biological macromolecule that is the disposition to participate in adherence to a host.

rdfs:label: invasion disposition
IAO:0000115: A disposition borne by a biological macromolecule that is the disposition to facilitate breach of host epithelial barriers or entry into and survival in host cells.

rdfs:label: antimicrobial disposition
IAO:0000115: A disposition to kill or inhibit the development or reproduction of microorganisms.

rdfs:label: antiviral disposition
IAO:0000115: A disposition to kill or inhibit the lifecycle of viruses.

rdfs:label: antifungal disposition
IAO:0000115: A disposition to kill or inhibit the development or reproduction of fungal organisms.

rdfs:label: antibacterial disposition
IAO:0000115: A disposition to kill or inhibit the reproduction of bacteria.

rdfs:label: antiparasitic disposition
IAO:0000115: A disposition to kill or inhibit the development or reproduction of eukaryotic parasites.

rdfs:label: protective resistance
IAO:0000115: A disposition that inheres in a material entity in virtue of the fact that the entity has a part (e.g. a gene product), which itself has a disposition to mitigate damage to the entity.

rdfs:label: pathogenic disposition
IAO:0000115: A disposition to initiate processes that result in a disorder.

rdfs:label: invasive disposition
IAO:0000115: A disposition borne by an infectious agent that is the disposition to penetrate the epithelial barriers of an organism of another Species.

rdfs:label: collective disposition
IAO:0000115: A disposition that inheres in a collection of entities in virtue of the individual dispositions of the constituents of that collection.

rdfs:label: contagiousness
IAO:0000115: A disposition that inheres in a host of infectious agent and is a disposition to transmit infectious agents to organisms of the same Species through casual contact with a high likelihood of realization.

rdfs:label: immunocompetence
IAO:0000115: A disposition that is the ability to mount a normal immune response.

rdfs:label: immunosuppressive disposition
IAO:0000115: A disposition whose realization negatively regulates an immune response.

rdfs:label: disposition to form a non-parasitic colony
IAO:0000115: A disposition to colonize an organism and participate in mutualism or commensalism with that organism.

rdfs:label: transmissibility disposition
IAO:0000115: A disposition to undergo a transmission process.

rdfs:label: parasitic disposition
IAO:0000115: A disposition to participate in a process of symbiosis in which the bearer derives a growth, survival, or fitness advantage from symbiosis while the other symbiont's growth, survival, or fitness is reduced.

rdfs:label: disease
IAO:0000115: A disposition (i) to undergo pathological processes that (ii) exists in an organism because of one or more disorders in that organism.

rdfs:label: symbiont role
IAO:0000115: A role borne by an organism in symbiosis.

rdfs:label: pathogen role
IAO:0000115: A role borne by pathogen in virtue of the fact that it or one of its products is sufficiently close to an organism towards which it has the pathogenic disposition to allow realization of the pathogenic disposition.

rdfs:label: infectious agent transporter role
IAO:0000115: A role borne by a material entity in virtue of the fact that an infectious agent is located in or on the entity and the entity has the capability to transfer (either actively or passively) the infectious agent from one location to another.

rdfs:label: reservoir of infectious agent role
IAO:0000115: A role borne by a material entity in virtue of the fact that it is a habitat in which infectious agents can persist and multiply and from which they can be transmitted in virtue of prevailing practices of potential hosts.

rdfs:label: infectious agent portal of entry role
IAO:0000115: A role borne by an anatomical entity in virtue of the fact that it serves as the site through which an infectious agent enters a host.

rdfs:label: infectious agent portal of exit role
IAO:0000115: A role borne by an anatomical entity in virtue of the fact that it serves as the site through which an infectious agent exits a host.

rdfs:label: disinfectant role
IAO:0000115: A role borne by a material entity in virtue of the fact that it has an antimicrobial disposition and is applied to a non-living entity.

rdfs:label: antiseptic role
IAO:0000115: A role borne by a material entity in virtue of the fact that it has an antimicrobial disposition and is applied to an anatomical entity of a living organism.

rdfs:label: primary infection role
IAO:0000115: A role borne by an infectious disorder in virtue of the fact that (1) the host has at least two distinct infectious disorders, where neither arose from the other through metastasis, (2) at the time the infectious disorder was established in the host, the host had no infectious disorder, and (3) the infectious disorder increases the host's susceptibility to infectious disorders.

rdfs:label: secondary infection role
IAO:0000115: A role borne by an infectious disorder in virtue of the fact that (1) the host has at least two distinct infectious disorders, where neither arose from the other through metastasis, (2) at the time the infectious disorder was established in the host, the host had a primary infectious disorder, and (3) establishment of the infectious disorder occurs because of increased susceptibility to infectious disorders conferred by the primary infectious disorder.

rdfs:label: host role
IAO:0000115: A role borne by an organism in virtue of the fact that it's extended organism contains a material entity other than the organism.

rdfs:label: source of infection role
IAO:0000115: A role borne by a material entity in virtue of the fact that it contains a site from which an infectious agent is transmitted.

rdfs:label: susceptibility to infectious agent
IAO:0000115: A susceptibility that inheres in an organism and is the degree to which it can be harmed by an infectious agent.

rdfs:label: drug susceptibility
IAO:0000115: A susceptibility that is the degree to which an entity can be harmed or inhibited from surviving by a drug.

rdfs:label: infectious disease endemic rate
IAO:0000115: An infectious disease incidence rate that is typical for an infectious disease in an organism population.

rdfs:label: infectious disease endemic level
IAO:0000115: An infectious disease prevalence that is typical for an infectious disease in an organism population.

rdfs:label: infectious disease hyper-endemicity
IAO:0000115: An infectious disease endemicity that inheres in an organism population in virtue of the fact that the infectious disease endemic level for an infectious disease is persistently high in the population.

rdfs:label: data about an ontology part
IAO:0000115: data about an ontology part is a data item about a part of an ontology, for example a term

rdfs:label: FtsZ-dependent cytokinesis
IAO:0000115: A cytokinesis process that involves a set of conserved proteins including FtsZ, and results in the formation of two similarly sized and shaped cells.

rdfs:label: adaptive immune response
IAO:0000115: An immune response mediated by cells expressing specific receptors for antigen produced through a somatic diversification process, and allowing for an enhanced secondary response to subsequent exposures to the same antigen (immunological memory).

rdfs:label: leukocyte mediated immunity
IAO:0000115: Any process involved in the carrying out of an immune response by a leukocyte.

rdfs:label: humoral immune response
IAO:0000115: An immune response mediated through a body fluid.

rdfs:label: innate immune response
IAO:0000115: Innate immune responses are defense responses mediated by germline encoded components that directly recognize components of potential pathogens.

rdfs:label: establishment of localization in host
IAO:0000115: An establishment of localization process in which a material entity reaches a site in an organism in which it can survive, grow, multiply, or mature.

rdfs:label: symbiosis, encompassing mutualism through parasitism
IAO:0000115: An interaction between two organisms living together in more or less intimate association. Microscopic symbionts are often referred to as endosymbionts. The various forms of symbiosis include parasitism, in which the association is disadvantageous or destructive to one of the organisms; mutualism, in which the association is advantageous, or often necessary to one or both and not harmful to either; and commensalism, in which one member of the association benefits while the other is not affected. However, mutualism, parasitism, and commensalism are often not discrete categories of interactions and should rather be perceived as a continuum of interaction ranging from parasitism to mutualism. In fact, the direction of a symbiotic interaction can change during the lifetime of the symbionts due to developmental changes as well as changes in the biotic/abiotic environment in which the interaction occurs.

rdfs:label: entry into host
IAO:0000115: Penetration by an organism into the body, tissues, or cells of the host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

rdfs:label: vaccination against infectious agent
IAO:0000115: An active immunization that begins with exposure of an organism to a vaccine.

rdfs:label: variolation
IAO:0000115: An active immunization that begins with exposure to smallpox in the form of a scab from a pustule and results in immunity against smallpox.

rdfs:label: infection-based immunosuppression
IAO:0000115: A pathologic immunosuppression process which arises as the result of an infection and is initiated or dysregulated by the infectious agent population.

rdfs:label: drug-based immunosuppression
IAO:0000115: A pathologic immunosuppression process which arises as the result of treatment with a drug that attenuates immune responses.

rdfs:label: host living with infected household contact
IAO:0000115: A host exposure to environment with infectious agent where the environment is a household that also has an infected host

rdfs:label: host living in endemic area
IAO:0000115: A host exposure to environment with infectious agent where the environment is an area in which an infectious agent is endemic

rdfs:label: release of infectious human pathogen in laboratory
IAO:0000115: A host exposure to environment with infectious agent where the exposure is accidental; the environment is a laboratory, and the infectious agent is infectious in humans.

rdfs:label: host coming into contact with vector of infectious agent
IAO:0000115: A host exposure to environment with infectious agent where the environment contains an infectious agent vector.

rdfs:label: host exposure to substance that might have infectious agent
IAO:0000115: A host exposure to environment with infectious agent where the environment contains a material entity that has been assessed to confer a risk of infection.

rdfs:label: acute infectious disease course
IAO:0000115: An infectious disease course that begins soon after infection is established and progresses rapidly to severe stages.

rdfs:label: chronic infectious disease course
IAO:0000115: An infectious disease course that unfolds over a long period of time.

rdfs:label: infected population
IAO:0000115: An organism population whose members have an infection.

rdfs:label: diseased population
IAO:0000115: An organism population in whose members an infectious disease is being realized.

rdfs:label: infectious agent population
IAO:0000115: An organism population whose members each have an infectious disposition.

rdfs:label: susceptible population
IAO:0000115: An organism population whose members are not infected with an infectious agent and who lack immunity to the infectious agent.

rdfs:label: normal resident microbiota population
IAO:0000115: An organism population whose members are participating in non-parasitic symbiosis with a particular host.

rdfs:label: immune population
IAO:0000115: An organism population whose members have acquired immunity to an infectious agent.

rdfs:label: colony
IAO:0000115: An organism population persisting in a site it has colonized.

rdfs:label: leukocyte
IAO:0000115: An achromatic cell of the myeloid or lymphoid lineages capable of ameboid movement, found in blood or other tissue.

rdfs:label: exotoxin
IAO:0000115: A molecular entity bearing an exotoxin disposition.

rdfs:label: endotoxin
IAO:0000115: A molecular entity with a toxin disposition and that is a structural component of a pathogen and is released from the pathogen only upon cytolysis.

rdfs:label: cytotoxin
IAO:0000115: A molecular entity with a toxin disposition, the realization of which damages host cells.

rdfs:label: neurotoxin
IAO:0000115: A molecular entity with a toxin disposition, the realization of which damages or interferes with the function of nerve tissue.

rdfs:label: primary pathogen
IAO:0000115: An infectious agent with a primary infectious disposition.

rdfs:label: emerging pathogen
IAO:0000115: An infectious agent whose infection incidence is increasing following its first introduction into a new host Species.

rdfs:label: infectious human pathogen
IAO:0000115: An infectious agent with a capability to infect human hosts.

rdfs:label: re-emerging pathogen
IAO:0000115: An infectious agent whose infection incidence is increasing in a host population as a result of changes in the biology of the host or pathogen, or changes in their interactions.

rdfs:label: opportunistic pathogen
IAO:0000115: An infectious agent with an opportunistic infectious disposition.

rdfs:label: viremia
IAO:0000115: An infection that has as part virus particles located in the blood.

rdfs:label: bacteremia
IAO:0000115: An infection that has as part bacteria located in the blood.

rdfs:label: focal infection
IAO:0000115: A local infection for which symptoms are observed in parts of the host's extended organism that are distant from the infection.

rdfs:label: primary infection
IAO:0000115: An infection bearing the primary infection role.

rdfs:label: secondary infection
IAO:0000115: An infection bearing the secondary infection role.

rdfs:label: acute infection
IAO:0000115: An infectious disorder that is the physical basis for an unfolding acute infectious disease course.

rdfs:label: pathologically immunosuppressed organism
IAO:0000115: An immunosuppressed organism that is experiencing pathologic immunosuppression.

rdfs:label: co-infected organism
IAO:0000115: An organism that has two infections with distinct Species of infectious agents.

rdfs:label: obligatory symbiont
IAO:0000115: An organism that can only reach developmental maturity, replicate, or persist in symbiosis.

rdfs:label: mutualist
IAO:0000115: An organism bearing a mutualist role.

rdfs:label: commensal
IAO:0000115: An organism bearing a commensal role.

rdfs:label: parasite
IAO:0000115: A organism bearing a parasite role.

rdfs:label: definitive host
IAO:0000115: An organism bearing a definitive host role.

rdfs:label: intermediate host
IAO:0000115: A organism bearing an intermediate host role.

rdfs:label: paratenic host
IAO:0000115: An organism bearing a paratenic host role.

rdfs:label: dead-end host
IAO:0000115: An organism bearing a dead-end host role.

rdfs:label: parasite host
IAO:0000115: An organism bearing a parasite host role.

rdfs:label: pathogen host
IAO:0000115: An organism bearing a pathogen host role.

rdfs:label: mechanical vector of infectious agent
IAO:0000115: An infectious agent vector bearing a mechanical vector of infectious agent role.

rdfs:label: biological vector of infectious agent
IAO:0000115: An infectious agent vector bearing a biological vector of infectious agent role.

rdfs:label: virion
IAO:0000115: A virus that is in its assembled state consisting of genomic material (DNA or RNA) surrounded by coating molecules.

rdfs:label: acquired immunodeficiency
IAO:0000115: An immunodeficiency that is not caused by a genetic predisposition.

rdfs:label: primary immunodeficiency
IAO:0000115: An immunodeficiency that exists in an organism because of a genetic predisposition.

rdfs:label: exotoxin disposition
IAO:0000115: A toxin disposition to damage cells or extracellular matrix by a direct enzymatic process.

rdfs:label: resistance to drug
IAO:0000115: A protective resistance that mitigates the damaging effects of a drug.

rdfs:label: resistance to infectious agent
IAO:0000115: A protective resistance that inheres in an organism and mitigates the damaging effects on that organism of an infectious agent.

rdfs:label: infectious disposition
IAO:0000115: A pathogenic disposition that inheres in an organism and is a disposition for that organism (1) to be transmitted to a host, (2) to establish itself in the host, (3) to initiate processes that result in a disorder in the host, and (4) to become part of that disorder.

rdfs:label: human pathogenicity disposition
IAO:0000115: A disposition to initiate processes that result in a disorder in a human organism.

rdfs:label: collective pathogenic disposition
IAO:0000115: A collective disposition to initiate processes that result in a disorder.

rdfs:label: collective resistance disposition
IAO:0000115: A collective disposition the realization of which mitigates the damaging effects of some entity on members of the collection.

rdfs:label: infectious disease
IAO:0000115: A disease whose physical basis is an infectious disorder.

rdfs:label: mutualist role
IAO:0000115: A symbiont role borne by an organism in virtue of the fact that both symbionts derive a growth, survival, or fitness advantage from symbiosis.

rdfs:label: commensal role
IAO:0000115: A symbiont role borne by an organism in virtue of the fact that it derives a growth, survival, or fitness advantage from symbiosis, but the other symbiont is neither advantaged nor disadvantaged.

rdfs:label: parasite role
IAO:0000115: A symbiont role borne by an organism in virtue of the fact that it derives a growth, survival, or fitness advantage from symbiosis while the other symbiont's growth, survival, or fitness is reduced.

rdfs:label: infectious agent role
IAO:0000115: A role borne by an infectious agent when contained in a host in which its infectious disposition can be realized.

rdfs:label: infectious agent vector role
IAO:0000115: An infectious agent transporter role that is borne by an organism active in the transfer of an infectious agent to an organism of another Species and in which the agent is infectious.

rdfs:label: infectious agent vehicle role
IAO:0000115: An infectious agent transporter role borne by an entity in virtue of the fact that the entity is not a complete organism.

rdfs:label: symbiont host role
IAO:0000115: A host role borne by an organism in virtue of the fact that its extended organism contains a second organism and provides an environment supportive for the survival, growth, maturation, or reproduction of that organism.

rdfs:label: pathogen host role
IAO:0000115: A host role borne by an organism in virtue of the fact that its extended organism contains a pathogen.

rdfs:label: drug susceptibility of infectious agent
IAO:0000115: A drug susceptibility that inheres in an infectious agent and is the degree to which the infectious agent can be harmed or inhibited from surviving by a drug.

rdfs:label: curation status specification
IAO:0000115: The curation status of the term. The allowed values come from an enumerated list of predefined terms. See the specification of these instances for more detailed definitions of each enumerated value.

rdfs:label: obsolescence reason specification
IAO:0000115: The reason for which a term has been deprecated. The allowed values come from an enumerated list of predefined terms. See the specification of these instances for more detailed definitions of each enumerated value.

rdfs:label: denotator type
IAO:0000115: A denotator type indicates how a term should be interpreted from an ontological perspective.

rdfs:label: colonization of host
IAO:0000115: An establishment of localization in host process in which an organism establishes itself in a host.

rdfs:label: mutualism
IAO:0000115: An interaction between two organisms living together in more or less intimate association in a relationship in which both organisms benefit from each other.

rdfs:label: commensalism
IAO:0000115: An interaction between two organisms living together in more or less intimate association in a relationship in which one benefits and the other is unaffected.

rdfs:label: entry into host through host barriers
IAO:0000115: Penetration by an organism into its host organism via active breaching of the physical barriers of the host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

rdfs:label: HIV-based immunosuppression
IAO:0000115: An infection-based immunosuppression process which arises as the result of an HIV infection.

rdfs:label: chronic systemic steroid use-based immunosuppression
IAO:0000115: A drug-based immunosuppression process that results from chronic systemic steroid use.

rdfs:label: long-term non-progressing infectious disease course
IAO:0000115: A chronic infectious disease course that does not progress to severe stages for a long period of time.

rdfs:label: infectious agent colony
IAO:0000115: A colony whose members are infectious agents.

rdfs:label: enterotoxin
IAO:0000115: A molecular entity with an exotoxin disposition, the realization of which damages cells of the host intestinal mucosa.

rdfs:label: immunosuppressed organism experiencing infection-based immunosuppression
IAO:0000115: A pathologically immunosuppressed organism that is experiencing infection-based immunosuppression.

rdfs:label: immunosuppressed organism experiencing drug-based immunosuppression
IAO:0000115: A pathologically immunosuppressed organism that is experiencing drug-based immunosuppression.

rdfs:label: infectious agent host
IAO:0000115: An organism bearing an infectious agent host role.

rdfs:label: antibiotic resistance
IAO:0000115: A resistance to drug that mitigates the damaging effects of an antibiotic.

rdfs:label: immunity to infectious agent
IAO:0000115: A resistance to infectious agent that inheres in an organism in virtue of immune system components in the extended organism.

rdfs:label: genetic resistance to infectious agent
IAO:0000115: A resistance to infectious agent that inheres in an organism in virtue of a specific allele or combination of alleles in its genome.

rdfs:label: opportunistic infectious disposition
IAO:0000115: An infectious disposition to become part of a disorder only in organisms whose defenses are compromised.

rdfs:label: primary infectious disposition
IAO:0000115: An infectious disposition to become part of a disorder in organisms that have intact defenses.

rdfs:label: zoonotic disposition
IAO:0000115: An infectious disposition that is the disposition to be transmitted from an infected, non-human host to a human host.

rdfs:label: reverse zoonotic disposition
IAO:0000115: An infectious disposition that is the disposition to be transmitted from an infected, human host to a non-human host.

rdfs:label: communicability
IAO:0000115: An infectious disposition to be transmitted directly from one organism to another of the same Species by horizontal transmission.

rdfs:label: herd immunity to infectious organism
IAO:0000115: A collective resistance disposition that inheres in an organism population in virtue of the fact that the proportion of the population with immunity to an infectious agent is high resulting in a low number of transmissions from hosts in the population to susceptible individuals in the population and thereby mitigating the damaging effects of the infectious agent on the population.

rdfs:label: zoonosis
IAO:0000115: An infectious disease that has as its physical basis an infectious disorder composed of infectious agents that have a zoonotic disposition.

rdfs:label: reverse zoonosis
IAO:0000115: An infectious disease that has as its physical basis an infectious disorder composed of infectious agents that have a reverse zoonotic disposition.

rdfs:label: mechanical vector of infectious agent role
IAO:0000115: An infectious agent vector role borne by an organism in virtue of the fact that the infectious agent does not multiply in or on the vector.

rdfs:label: biological vector of infectious agent role
IAO:0000115: An infectious agent vector role borne by an organism in virtue of the fact that the infectious agent multiplies in the vector.

rdfs:label: biological vehicle of infectious agent role
IAO:0000115: An infectious agent vehicle role borne by an entity in virtue of the fact that the entity is living or contains living cells other than those that have the infectious disposition.

rdfs:label: fomite role
IAO:0000115: An infectious agent vehicle role borne by an entity in virtue of the fact that the entity is not alive.

rdfs:label: definitive host role
IAO:0000115: A symbiont host role borne by an organism in virtue of the fact that its partner in symbiosis reaches developmental maturity or reproduces sexually in the host.

rdfs:label: intermediate host role
IAO:0000115: A symbiont host role borne by an organism in virtue of the fact that its partner in symbiosis utilizes the host to undergo a developmental stage transition, and the host is required for continuation of the partner's life cycle.

rdfs:label: paratenic host role
IAO:0000115: A symbiont host role borne by an organism in virtue of the fact that its partner in symbiosis utilizes the host to undergo a developmental stage transition, but the host is not required for continuation of the partner's life cycle.

rdfs:label: dead-end host role
IAO:0000115: A symbiont host role borne by an organism in virtue of the fact that its partner in symbiosis has the infectious disposition but cannot be transmitted from the host to the partner's definitive host.

rdfs:label: parasite host role
IAO:0000115: A symbiont host role borne by an organism in virtue of the fact that its partner in symbiosis derives from the host a growth, survival, or fitness advantage while the host's growth, survival, or fitness is reduced.

rdfs:label: infectious agent host role
IAO:0000115: A pathogen host role borne by an organism in virtue of the fact that its extended organism contains an infectious agent.

rdfs:label: establishment of a clinically abnormal colony
IAO:0000115: A colonization of host process that results in a clinically abnormal colony.

rdfs:label: colonization of human
IAO:0000115: A colonization of host process in which the host is of Species Homo sapiens.

rdfs:label: immunosuppressed organism experiencing HIV-based immunosuppression
IAO:0000115: A pathologically immunosuppressed organism that is experiencing HIV-based immunosuppression.

rdfs:label: immunosuppressed organism experiencing chronic systemic steroid use-based immunosuppression
IAO:0000115: a pathologically immunosuppressed organism that is experiencing chronic systemic steroid use-based immunosuppression.

rdfs:label: immunosuppressed human experiencing drug-based immunosuppression due to organ transplant
IAO:0000115: A pathologically immunosuppressed organism that is a human experiencing drug-based immunosuppression.

rdfs:label: infectious agent carrier
IAO:0000115: An organism bearing the infectious agent carrier role.

rdfs:label: asymptomatic host of infectious agent
IAO:0000115: An organism that is host to an infectious agent and has no symptoms of the infectious disease associated with the infectious agent.

rdfs:label: symptomatic host of infectious agent
IAO:0000115: An organism who is host to an infectious agent and has symptoms of the infectious disease associated with the infectious agent

rdfs:label: sterilizing immunity to infectious agent
IAO:0000115: An immunity to infectious agent that results in elimination of the infectious agent from the host.

rdfs:label: innate immunity to infectious agent
IAO:0000115: An immunity to infectious agent that inheres in an organism in virtue of germline encoded components that directly recognize components of potential pathogens.

rdfs:label: humoral immunity to infectious agent
IAO:0000115: An immunity to infectious agent that inheres in an organism in virtue of components of its circulating body fluid.

rdfs:label: leukocyte-mediated immunity to infectious agent
IAO:0000115: An immunity to infectious agent that inheres in an organism in virtue of its leukocytes.

rdfs:label: passive immunity to infectious agent
IAO:0000115: An immunity to infectious agent that inheres in an organism in virtue of antibodies not produced by that organism.

rdfs:label: acquired immunity to infectious agent
IAO:0000115: An immunity to infectious agent that inheres in an organism in virtue of antigen receptors encoded by somatically diversified genes in the organism's genome and expressed by cells that have undergone selection during a primary immune response in that organism.

rdfs:label: infectious agent carrier role
IAO:0000115: An infectious agent host role borne by an organism in virtue of the fact that its extended organism contains an infectious agent, the infectious agent has the infectious disposition towards the host, and the host has no symptoms of the infectious disease caused by the infectious agent.

rdfs:label: colonization of human anterior nares
IAO:0000115: A colonization of human process in which the colonized site is the anterior nares.

rdfs:label: colonization of human perineum
IAO:0000115: A colonization of human process in which the colonized site is a perineum.

rdfs:label: immunosuppressed human experiencing HIV-based immunosuppression
IAO:0000115: An immunosuppressed organism that is a human experiencing HIV-based immunosuppression.

rdfs:label: immunosuppressed human experiencing chronic systemic steroid use-based immunosuppression
IAO:0000115: An immunosuppressed organism that is a human experiencing chronic systemic steroid use-based immunosuppression.

rdfs:label: chronic carrier of infectious agent
IAO:0000115: An organism who has been bearer of the infectious agent carrier role for an extended period of time.
